        "title": "fix(doctor): respect explicit PI runtime policy",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nRespect explicit PI/OpenClaw runtime policy when Codex is intentionally disabled.\n\nThis keeps the existing OpenAI/Codex default behavior unchanged, but makes explicit PI config authoritative in two places:\n\n- config validation no longer emits a missing `@openclaw/codex` install warning when OpenAI routes are explicitly pinned to PI and no Codex runtime is configured\n- doctor session route repair preserves explicit PI/OpenClaw session runtime pins while rewriting stale `openai-codex/*` route metadata to canonical `openai/*`\n\n## Tests\n\n- `pnpm test -- --run src/config/config.plugin-validation.test.ts src/commands/doctor/shared/codex-route-warnings.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `pnpm lint:core`\n\nRefs #88706.\n",
